Description: Software designed for the budding industries of commercial hemp and CBD production and tracking.
Full Description: Hemp has come a long way. It has come out of the shadow of Cannabis to become one of this and next year's hottest industries. While industry has plowed ahead making progress on how to plant, harvest, and process hemp into hundreds of products, what has not progressed is regulation. We believe, and so does everyone else, quite frankly, that when regulations finally show up, many bad habits are going to have been created inside of the industry. What we set out to do was provide good habits. A way to track seed certifications, THC tests, transporations chains of custodies, and proof of origins for the entire industry. This way, when regulations do show up, the right habits are already being practiced, and no lag time for compliance is needed. HempTracker helps track all the necessary documentation to make you legal, and to make your product's origin trackable (example: Nebraska certidfied hemp). It has multiple different log-ins including one for: farmers, processesers/manufacturers, labs, law enforcement, retailers, and buyers.

Description: The New Media Consortium, a community of universities, museums, and research centers, stimulates the use of technology for learning.
Full Description: The New Media Consortium (NMC) is a community of universities, colleges, museums, and research centers that stimulates the exploration and use of new media and technologies for educational purposes. It conducts research that catalyzes discussion, convenes people around new ideas, and builds communities that encourages exploration and experimentation. Members are updated about the NMC’s activities via social media platforms and electronic newsletters. The NMC conducts targeted research on a wide range of emerging ideas and technologies, including visual literacy, Challenge Based Learning, virtual worlds, learning objects, and more. The NMC Horizon Project, the NMC’s flagship research effort, has produced the NMC Horizon Report series for a decade, with a readership of over 1.25 million. The NMC hosts events, conferences, and meetings, and workshops to offer members with opportunities to interact with each other. It organizes more than 30 virtual meetings per year to provide members with opportunities to interact with thought leaders, learn from each other, and showcase their projects. The annual face-to-face meeting of the Campus Leaders Advisory Board enables members to guide the agenda and goals of the NMC for the coming year. UNESCO, OECD, World Bank, USAID, United Nations University, JISC, Singapore IDA, the Education World Forum, and WISE are some the organizations that work with the NMC. The New Media Consortium was founded on October 17, 1993, and is based in Texas, United States.
